-- Wendy's Plans Up to $20 Million in Caucusus Restaurants
-- B y   H e l e n a   B e d w e l l
-- 2012-04-05T19:48:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-05/wendy-s-plans-up-to-20-million-in-caucusus-restaurants.html
Wendy’s Co. (WEN)  plans to open as many as
25 restaurants in  Georgia  and  Azerbaijan  in an agreement with
Wissol Group in a $10 million to $20 million investment, Darrell
Van Ligten, senior vice president for strategic development,
said in an interview in Tbilisi, Georgia, today.  “Georgia is a dynamic market with long-term growth
potential for the brand,” Van Ligten said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Helena Bedwell in Tbilisi at 
 hbedwell@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Greg Chang at 
 gchang1@bloomberg.net  